<subSubSection id="C30B655C4B028139BEB16CCCFB4F94D3" pageId="9" pageNumber="568" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BAE36D74B028139BEB16CCCFB4F94D3" blockId="9.[151,1437,464,707]" pageId="9" pageNumber="568">
<emphasis id="B965EAC54B028139BEB16CCCFEDD941F" bold="true" box="[199,365,500,526]" pageId="9" pageNumber="568">Redescription</emphasis>
. Body U–shaped; tube feet restricted to radii in double rows (
<figureCitation id="132A2A524B028139BA6B6CCCFBCD941E" box="[1053,1149,500,527]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1807,1831]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,711,1787]" captionTargetId="figure-256@9.[151,1435,711,1789]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 10. Cladolella virgo Heding &amp; Panning, 1954, (ZMUC-HOL 256). (a) specimen in dorsal view; (b) muscular system; (c) photograph of the calcareous ring in lateral view; (d) drawing of the calcareous ring (extracted from Heding &amp; Panning, 1954 and (e) rods from body wall. Abbreviations: PV, Polian vesicle; AP, anterior projection." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6392930" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6392930/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="568">Fig. 10a</figureCitation>
). Color, in ethanol, beige. 20 dendritic tentacles arranged in 2 circles (10 + 10): 
<quantity id="4CE99B324B028139BC906F21FCAE9423" box="[742,798,536,563]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="9" pageNumber="568" unit="in" value="10.0">10 in</quantity>
outer circle and 10 smaller in inner circle (
<figureCitation id="132A2A524B028139BA8E6F20FAE99422" box="[1272,1369,536,563]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1807,1831]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,711,1787]" captionTargetId="figure-256@9.[151,1435,711,1789]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 10. Cladolella virgo Heding &amp; Panning, 1954, (ZMUC-HOL 256). (a) specimen in dorsal view; (b) muscular system; (c) photograph of the calcareous ring in lateral view; (d) drawing of the calcareous ring (extracted from Heding &amp; Panning, 1954 and (e) rods from body wall. Abbreviations: PV, Polian vesicle; AP, anterior projection." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6392930" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6392930/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="568">Fig. 10b</figureCitation>
). Two Polian vesicles (
<figureCitation id="132A2A524B028139BF266F04FE019446" box="[336,433,572,599]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1807,1831]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,711,1787]" captionTargetId="figure-256@9.[151,1435,711,1789]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 10. Cladolella virgo Heding &amp; Panning, 1954, (ZMUC-HOL 256). (a) specimen in dorsal view; (b) muscular system; (c) photograph of the calcareous ring in lateral view; (d) drawing of the calcareous ring (extracted from Heding &amp; Panning, 1954 and (e) rods from body wall. Abbreviations: PV, Polian vesicle; AP, anterior projection." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6392930" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6392930/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="568">Fig. 10c</figureCitation>
). Radial and interradial plates of calcareous ring fused. Radial plates subdivided, rectangular, with posterior projection and 2 AP (
<figureCitation id="132A2A524B028139BC0E6F58FD6B946A" box="[632,731,608,635]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1807,1831]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,711,1787]" captionTargetId="figure-256@9.[151,1435,711,1789]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 10. Cladolella virgo Heding &amp; Panning, 1954, (ZMUC-HOL 256). (a) specimen in dorsal view; (b) muscular system; (c) photograph of the calcareous ring in lateral view; (d) drawing of the calcareous ring (extracted from Heding &amp; Panning, 1954 and (e) rods from body wall. Abbreviations: PV, Polian vesicle; AP, anterior projection." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6392930" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6392930/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="568">Fig. 10d</figureCitation>
). Interradial plates arrow shaped. Radial and interradial plates lacking posterior processes (
<figureCitation id="132A2A524B028139BFAC6FBCFD8D948E" box="[474,573,644,671]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1807,1831]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,711,1787]" captionTargetId="figure-256@9.[151,1435,711,1789]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 10. Cladolella virgo Heding &amp; Panning, 1954, (ZMUC-HOL 256). (a) specimen in dorsal view; (b) muscular system; (c) photograph of the calcareous ring in lateral view; (d) drawing of the calcareous ring (extracted from Heding &amp; Panning, 1954 and (e) rods from body wall. Abbreviations: PV, Polian vesicle; AP, anterior projection." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6392930" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6392930/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="568">Fig. 10d</figureCitation>
). Body wall ossicles as rods, stellate at one end (with about six projections) and twelve at the other end (
<figureCitation id="132A2A524B028139BFA36F90FD8594D2" box="[469,565,680,707]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1807,1831]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,711,1787]" captionTargetId="figure-256@9.[151,1435,711,1789]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 10. Cladolella virgo Heding &amp; Panning, 1954, (ZMUC-HOL 256). (a) specimen in dorsal view; (b) muscular system; (c) photograph of the calcareous ring in lateral view; (d) drawing of the calcareous ring (extracted from Heding &amp; Panning, 1954 and (e) rods from body wall. Abbreviations: PV, Polian vesicle; AP, anterior projection." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6392930" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6392930/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="568">Fig. 10e</figureCitation>
). Tube feet with two–pillared tables, arched disc, and end plate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF6E665F4B028139BEE16A37FBBC9161" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6392930" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6392930" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6392930/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="568" startId="9.[151,250,1807,1831]" targetBox="[151,1435,711,1787]" targetPageId="9">
<paragraph id="8BAE36D74B028139BEE16A37FBBC9161" blockId="9.[151,1437,1807,1904]" pageId="9" pageNumber="568">
<emphasis id="B965EAC54B028139BEE16A37FEAF9136" bold="true" box="[151,287,1807,1831]" pageId="9" pageNumber="568">FIGURE 10.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C114D544B028139BF536A28FD7E9136" authority="Heding &amp; Panning, 1954" authorityName="Heding &amp; Panning" authorityYear="1954" box="[293,718,1807,1832]" class="Holothuroidea" family="Phyllophoridae" genus="Cladolella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dendrochirotida" pageId="9" pageNumber="568" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="virgo">
<emphasis id="B965EAC54B028139BF536A28FE7B9136" box="[293,459,1808,1832]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="568">Cladolella virgo</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF804B264B028139BFA66A28FD7E9136" author="Heding, S. G. &amp; Panning, A." box="[464,718,1807,1832]" pageId="9" pageNumber="568" pagination="7 - 209" refId="ref5809" refString="Heding, S. G. &amp; Panning, A. (1954) Phyllophoridae: eine Bearbeitung der Polytentaculaten Dendrochiroten Holothurien des Zoologischen Museums in Kopenhagen. Spolia Zoologica Musei Hauniensis, 13, 7 - 209." type="journal article" year="1954">Heding &amp; Panning, 1954</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, (ZMUC-HOL 256). (a) specimen in dorsal view; (b) muscular system; (c) photograph of the calcareous ring in lateral view; (d) drawing of the calcareous ring (extracted from 
<bibRefCitation id="EF804B264B028139BAD46A0CFA2D915A" author="Heding, S. G. &amp; Panning, A." box="[1186,1437,1843,1868]" pageId="9" pageNumber="568" pagination="7 - 209" refId="ref5809" refString="Heding, S. G. &amp; Panning, A. (1954) Phyllophoridae: eine Bearbeitung der Polytentaculaten Dendrochiroten Holothurien des Zoologischen Museums in Kopenhagen. Spolia Zoologica Musei Hauniensis, 13, 7 - 209." type="journal article" year="1954">Heding &amp; Panning, 1954</bibRefCitation>
and (e) rods from body wall. Abbreviations: PV, Polian vesicle; AP, anterior projection.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="C30B655C4B028139BEE16A81FD1291E6" pageId="9" pageNumber="568" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BAE36D74B028139BEE16A81FD1291E6" blockId="9.[151,1436,1976,2039]" pageId="9" pageNumber="568">
<emphasis id="B965EAC54B028139BEE16A81FEBB91C2" bold="true" box="[151,267,1977,2003]" pageId="9" pageNumber="568">Remarks.</emphasis>
The opportunity of examining the 
<typeStatus id="54AA88754B028139BCE56A80FD4591C3" box="[659,757,1976,2002]" pageId="9" pageNumber="568">holotype</typeStatus>
is taken to provide a photograph of the general aspect of the body (
